<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>In general...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?SirKronos">SirKronos</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:49 p.m. 30/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> In general...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>To start talking to an average NPC, what would one do? Hail them and hope they talk back, or do you ask a certain question? For example I started a quest in Halas as a Warrior talking to one guy that asks me to talk to Megan O'Rilley and ask about some guys remains. I followed him through his conversation, so that was cool. I just hailed him. But when I found the NPC in Everfrost I needed to speak to and hailed him, "Whew it's cold!", but when I said "Where is Megan?", he spoke like I needed. This confuses me... should I walk around to NPC's saying "Do you have a quest for me?" or what?

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
